title: More fun than I would’ve thought
text: I’m surprised I loved this place. It’s a farm of mostly deer and goats all wanting your snacks. There are a dozen of other species too. They have a fun gift shop too. I really enjoyed myself.

title: Square
text: It was interesting to see the buildings and learn a bit about the Mormon faith. There’s some great architectural features and facts.

title: Worth it
text: Lots of wildlife at dawn and dusk. Turkeys, quail, deer, elk and squirrels. Best photos between 9am-3pm. Get there early like before 8am or you’ll have to walk up or use the shuttle. It was unbelievable how even off season this was still true.

title: Wildlife and scenic sites
text: Lots of wildlife at dawn and dusk. Turkeys, quail, deer, elk and squirrels. Best photos between 9am-3pm. Get there early like before 8am or you’ll have to walk up or use the shuttle. It was unbelievable how even off season this was still true.

title: Quintessential Vegas
text: They now have fencing and separate parking for the sign. There’s also several signs of different designs throughout the city. This is the original and most popular. Be sure not to go at peak times like 6-9pm.
place: Welcome to Fabulous Las Vegas Sign

title: Worth it if you like dinos
text: It’s only 2.5 miles from I-15 freeway. There’s a few dozen footprints, tail prints, a few skeletons, and a butt print. It’s a great set up and worth a detour.
place: St. George Dinosaur Discovery Site at Johnson Farm

title: Ok if you like atvs
text: It’s not that pink. I’m sure if you are there at sunrise or sunset that it will look pink. There’s a nature trial that’s nice, but bring proper footwear since it’s in the sand. It says it’s the largest southwestern sand dunes in North America. Lots of ATVs.
place: Coral Pink Sand Dunes State Park

title: Awesome
text: It was awesome! Looking at old and not so old signs of Vegas history. Learned a few things about history and lore. I didn’t know there used to be segregation in Vegas. Totally worth it.

title: Faux but fun gondola ride
text: Is it a tour of an artificial canal inside a shopping mall made to look like the major sites in Venice? Yes. Was it fun and informative? Yes. It was worth it to me.

title: Not as nice as London’s
text: The ride is nice and smooth. The bummer is that the best views are at or near the top. The wheel is behind the linq so it’s industrial. There are car or vessels made for bar party which would be nice if you are part of a group. It’s cheap and low end in comparison to London millennium wheel.

title: Fun trip to the 1930s
text: This is a fun museum set in the courtroom for a major trial took place. There’s a sorts of memorabilia. Lots of fun.
place: Las Vegas Mob Museum Admission Ticket

title: Grand ole time
text: It was fun to see and actually play with old arcade games and the like. Some as old as the turn of the 20th century. Whether you like pin ball, video games, Nickelodeon’s, bar games and more.

title: Cant wait until it’s fully open
text: We went last year and it was just the lobby with a timeline, pictures and a few artifacts. I cannot wait until it’s open. History, plus costumes and props and more.
place: Skip the Line: Burlesque Hall of Fame Museum Admission Ticket

title: Tiny scenic harbor
text: I love parking here and watching the boats come in and go out. It’s pretty, quaint and serene. Great place to leave by water.

title: Just a cool old building of mystery
text: This is just an interesting old structure. No one knows who, when or why this was Built. It’s thought that the Vikings built it in the 14 or 15th century.

title: Best sweet treats
text: This is only open for half to three quarters of the year. It’s a sweet lemonade made with crushed ice. I wish this were available nationwide.

title: Sweet village w/historic homes
text: I love this quaint little village. It’s the perfect place in Rhode Island. There’s a harbor, yummy restaurants, cute shops, and lovely historic homes. The rune stone that’s believed to be inscribed by Vikings is there. Mostly I just love hanging out here.

title: Best roast beef and fish n chips
text: I wish that this would be a nationwide chain. They have great roast beef, as well as fish n chips (on Wednesday and Friday). Outside that it’s a homey fast food place.

title: Yachting history that’s fun
text: We went for the America’s Cup hall of fame. There’s boats, boat models, the people involved, history and so much more. The docent who grants entry was super knowledgeable and nice.

title: Quintessential New England beach
text: The beach is wide and long. Some places near by make it private. The beach is soft beige sand. Lovely view. Easy to get in and out of the water.

title: Bummed
text: I wanted to get lobster roll or something seafood to go and was shut out. Got a chocolate eclair that was tasty but chocolate cake everyone goes crazy about was sub par too me.

title: For the kid at heart
text: My inner child loved the waffle character out front beckoning customers. Food served to go or on site with part of the parking lot. The did a good job making it look like a patio setting. Food was fairly good.

title: Outdoor dining
text: With covid they smartly shut down the main street and had restaurants bring their tables outside. It was like a street fair atmosphere and a lovely way to eat dinner.

title: Pretty
text: We had fog roll in fast on this summer day. It was an awesome site to see. Also you can see this bridge from anywhere downtown or around the harbor.

title: Nice job handling covid
text: I loved they’re Covid response. The annoying part was the long line to get in with questions and temperature check for each guest. All trams tours and other group activities were gone for obvious reasons. However they marked social distance for line for entry. Once inside it was quite spacious and hardly a line anywhere. Did a good job.

title: Scenic and moving
text: The ground are immaculate. The views are stunning. You can see the bay and the ocean. You might get teary eyed knowing how many people died in service to our country...of course many lived to a ripe old age.

title: Scenic
text: Lovely place to go to enjoy the ocean. There’s a tide pool to check out all the creatures and a couple of beaches.

title: Great stroll
text: We took a private tuktuk powered by drivers bicycle up and down the promenade along the bay at night. Great place to exercise or Have a date.

title: Retro chic
text: The building was clearly built in the 60 or 70s., however, it’s completely renovated and cleverly decorated to Play up retro chic Factor. It’s right off the freeway, it’s inexpensive for San Diego there’s a great restaurant on property. It’s clean and quite. A winner of a property.

title: Nice for a quality inn
text: This is just outside the downtown area. Breakfast is across the street. Due to covid the buffet is not open. You get your choice of 2 options for hot food and you can order cold things like cereal or yogurt. Everything was wrapped in plastic at the hotel the towels, remote, everything.

title: Grateful
text: We drove from Arcadia National Park in northern Maine so it was quite late and there’s nothing but small towns and darkened streets. We were grateful to be able to check in here. The location is perfect near restaurants and a highway. Sure it’s older, but still clean and quiet. I’d stay again.

title: As expected, quite good
text: Just like any other in the chain you get what you expect. It’s clean, safe, quiet and easy access or distance from the freeway. The space of the room and room amenities exactly as advertised. This may sound blah to some, but when you are on the road this is a respite.
place: Fairfield Inn & Suites by Marriott Plymouth White Mountains

title: Delightful and delicious
text: My husband’s family used to come here when he was growing up. Everything is made from scratch. The mashed potatoes are the best in the USA in my opinion. I enjoyed the turkey nuggets with a delicious bbq sauce I hope to order. There’s also a carrot relish that was surprisingly tasty. I’d go again in a heartbeat.

title: Great balance for COVID concerns
text:
I loved and appreciated the covid response as a result I felt safe whilst got to ride the train. They have folks in every other row, so there’s was at least 6 feet between parties by 360 degrees.

The ride itself was really nice with some narration about the train, how it came to be, what we can see out the window, what we can when we get To the top, etc.

title: Not much to do or see
text: Because of COVID there’s no much to do or see. There’s an exhibit in the corridors leading up to the ordering windows and the grounds with a small gift shop. The ordering area has some unique flavors that one can’t easily find at your home grocery stores. You can see the flavor graveyard though. So it’s disappointing but understandable.

title: I finally got here
text: If you’re used to the parks in the west, this park isn’t like that. The coastline is pretty but the rest of the land is just like the region. This is a hikers paradise, great for cycling too. The horse carriage rides are fun way to tour the park.

title: Still able to learn without full experience
text: We went around the grounds, but can’t go inside due to COVID. It’s still really cool to be on the grounds and learn about the extreme weather. There’s all sorts of information about extreme weather on Mount Washington so you still feel like you get to visit.
place: Mount Washington Observatory Weather Discovery Center

title: Hard to visit during COVID
text: Visitor’s center last September was quite crowded. As a result there are small numbers that could get in. It’s a short steep hike up stairs from the parking lot.

title: Lovely building
text: Augusta is far from everything it’s not far from Portland but it’s a long drive for some reason. It’s not far from the freeway. The building it quite lovely.

title: Close to downtown for maple fun
text: It’s a cute tourist stop just minutes from downtown. There’s a video made by the previous generation owner, equipment from the process, serve serve and maple products, gift shop and more. The more isn’t known to me because COVID shut everything else down for the season. Be sure to check out the carvings.

title: Vermont state capitol
text: We only visited the outside the building and grounds. It’s a lovely building. The city has a small town feel with funky businesses.

title: Amazing
text: Definitely worth the time and money to see this. The history, architecture, how the history here impacts our daily lives today...just wow. By the way it’ll be hard to get a cab from here if you come at sunrise.

title: Very cool
text: This is some steep hiking and tons of stairs but totally worth it. Learning about the history of the area and how inhabitants lived is really something.

title: Original marathon
text: The battle of marathon results were once here. The messenger died after delivering the message (summer heat plus no water enroute was not good).

title: Interesting
text: We saw the changing of the guard. The outfits were interesting with the pom poms on top of the shoes and tights. Otherwise not worth it. All due respect.

title: Wow
text: I can’t believe that I stood in the cell that Socrates likely did. Now I can say, “they gave Socrates hemlock and they gave me you,” takes on a whole new dimension.

title: Opa!!
text: Scenic little piece of modernism history. It’s a great place to take pictures and it’s setting. Nice

title: Touristy but great
text: I love this town and especially at sunset. It’s touristy but so worth it. It’s gorgeous and peaceful with a great view.

title: Hot, hurt feet
text: This is a nice and popular beach. From May through August the black rocks are so hot it burns your skin and so rough it scratches the feet.

title: Interesting
text: I went for the history and unique factor. It’s steep and longer than I thought really hot in may. Otherwise interesting.

title: Photo opportunities
text: This is great for photos. It’s steep to get in and out and the beach is really rough in texture. I’d still go.

title: Gotta see this
text: So much fascinating history. The center of the ancient world. It’s very hot and uneven ground so be aware. The wildflowers in May was charming.

title: Fun learning
text: I liked looking at the evolution of the art from stiff figures to more life like. There’s all sort of interesting things here.

title: Best part of Delphi
text: I thought this was the best part of Delphi. Hearing the stories about gases from the earth marched out the ladies who gave prophecies so between that and everyone coming to you from the known world you were successful.

title: Gotta do it
text: This is the birthplace of the ancient olympics I loved Phineus’ workshop the temple for sues, and the amphitheater.

title: Wow
text: Most of the artifacts here are from this site. All the best stuff is in Athens, but that’s true of all of Greece. Loved it put the place in context and brings the site to life.

title: phineus
text: I loved seeing the birth place of the ancient Olympics. But my favorite bit, in addition to the museum and this whole place was seeing the remains of Phineus workshop.

title: Awesome ruins
text: Love the whole thing...the ruins, mosaics, the history, the ferry ride to get there. It’s all great. We were there in May and it was covered in wildflowers. Just wow.

title: Spellbound
text: I was enchanted, spellbound and gobsmacked by this place. Not only for the famous book of kells, but all the antique books and incredible long library.
place: Skip the Line: The Book of Kells Exhibition & Old Library Admission Ticket

title: Overpriced bars and restaurants
text: This is a nice area with plenty of nice locals and tons of tourists. All the shops, restaurants and bars are overpriced.

title: Same as other peninsulas
text: We did ring of Kerry and the dingle peninsulas. Dingle is prettier and has just as many quasi sites like barely there ruins. Don’t know why this is on every tour of Ireland.

title: Surprise
text: We were driving by and I saw the sign decided to see this on a lark. It’s a short walk to find these falls.

title: Not much
text: To call these ruins is an understatement. There’s not much here, but what there is, is quite interesting.

title: Fancy glass
text: Just a fancy glass factory. I wouldn’t go out of my way. However there are some rather nice things here.
place: House of Waterford Crystal Guided Factory Tour

title: More interesting than average
text: I liked all the history and exhibits here. There’s more to see and do than the average castle. Plus the cannon

title: Ruins with a view
text: In essence this is just a castle ruins with a view. The view is worth coming, not the ruins though..

title: Fine fun
text: Fine holiday fun. Local area history and exhibits and of course the Nessie legend. Worth a visit for fun.

title: Robin Hood fame
text: Came for the tale and enjoyed for the woods. Hard to believe this a historic woodland. Walking around is fun, recommend a guide who would point out things or bring the history to life.

title: Interesting collections
text: There were several interesting rooms and collections. I would not return, but there’s lots to see and do.

title: Go at sunrise
text: If you can, go at sunrise. We didn’t get to on a formal visit but arrived nearby and got some shots. Sure it’s a circle of rocks, but it’s pretty awesome. The history, the mystery the scenery...worth it.

title: National treasure
text: The history and who is interred here is amazing. The Abby is lovely and just fun to tour. I surisingly enjoyed it.

title: The best
text: I’ve been on other oversized Ferris wheels but this one is the best. Not just for the view, but the capsule designs, the surfer board shaped, antique looking wooden benches. Some are party or private capsules.

title: Nice
text: There’s many churches, so many tourist say ABC, another bloody church. This one feels steeped in history.

title: Fun
text: Helps bring the book to life. There’s dioramas and all sorts of exhibits to explore. I enjoyed this but it’s not for everyone.
place: The Canterbury Tales: Standard Day Entry

title: Auspicious location
text: I was with some older folks who stumbled a bit with the uneven ground. Impressive castle. I bet the kids love to explore this.

title: Spring time treat
text: This was absolutely beautiful in spring, may. The white chalk cliff with spring grass and colorful wildflowers. Great walk.

title: Scenic lighthouse
text: What A lovely setting for a lighthouse. Especially gorgeous in spring with the wildflowers abound. Wow

title: History
text: I’m a Roman history nut and enjoyed visiting this spot it’s amazing how much the were able to restore and preserve.

title: Church with a view
text: What a spectacular view and setting for this little chapel. The building is charming and the floor to ceiling wall of glass.
place: The Church of the Good Shepherd

title: Nice view
text: This is a nice ride with a well maintained gondola with great views of the area. Yet I didn’t feel compelled to repeat the experience or recommend to others.
